def has_cycle(head):
    if head is None or head.next is None:
        return False
    slow, fast = head, head
    while fast is not None and fast.next is not None:
        slow = slow.next
        fast = fast.next.next
        if slow is fast:
            return True
    return False

Uses Floyd's tortoise and hare. Time O(n), space O(1). Handles empty list, single node, and the no-cycle case via the fast pointer reaching None.
